===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|cneowlian|lang=ang}}, from {{term|cneow||lang=ang|knee}}; compare Goth. knussjan, Gk. gnyx "with bent knee." Past tense {{term|knelt}} is a modern formation (19c.) on analogy of {{term|feel}}/{{term|felt}}, etc.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|nēl}}, {{IPA|/niːl/}}, {{SAMPA|/ni:l/}}
* {{audio|en-us-kneel.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: {{rhymes|iːl}}
* {{homophones|Neal|Neil|Niel}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|kneels|kneeling|'''[[knelt]]''' ''or'' '''[[kneeled]]'''}}

# {{intransitive}} To [[stoop]] down and rest on the [[knee]] or knees.

